[Anthrax is routinely reported by OIE in the states of Maharashtra, Karnataka, and Andra Pradesh in significant numbers, and especially in the latter 2 states. Medak, in Andra Pradesh, is on the eastern border of north-eastern Karnataka. Where this itinerant flock of sheep and goats got infected is impossible to say but they could have been shedding carcasses en route for a week or so. Lateral spread of infection can occur from animals licking the salty blood from recently dead animals; I saw a similar situation in the UK with outbreaks every 8 days.

Drs Santosh Kumar, Deepankar, and Lakshma Reddy are to be congratulated on their rapid and thorough response.

Map of India showing Andra Pradesh, Karanataka, and Maharashtra:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_rel01.jpg
To find Medak district go to:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medak_district
and a Medak map with towns but not villages:
http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/andhrapradesh/districts/medak.htm

To see a video report on this outbreak, see:
http://metroslive.com/animals-died-due-to-anthrax-in-medak-dist-tv9/
- Mod.MHJ]
